AGI - Tragedy this morning on the ski slope of the 5 Torri-Falzarego-Lagazuoi ski area near Cortina d'Ampezzo. A 14-year-old English skier died after crashing into a tree.&nbsp;
The young skier lost his life after falling while skiing on the Lagazuoi-Col Gallina track. In the fall, the boy went out on track violently to slam against a tree.
&nbsp;
The police officers of the State Police of the detachment of skiers of Cortina d'Ampezzo equipped with the automatic defibrillator supplied and then the helicopter of the Suem 118 of Pieve di Cadore with on board the emergency doctor. After several reanimation attempts, the health caregivers declared the death of the fourteenth anniversary of the serious injuries reported in the impact.&nbsp;
